KANO – Barely 24 hours after Pro Osinbajo group wrapped up their historic meet in the ancient city of Kano, the National leader of All Progressives Congress, Asiwaju Ahmed Bola Tinubu stormed the one-city-state on Sunday evening on a condolence visit to families of prominent indigenes that died recently. The strongman of Nigerian politics had arrived at Aminu Kano International Airport on his private jet by 6:00 pm to the waiting arms of Kano governor, Dr. Abdullahi Umar Ganduje, member of his executive, party stalwart and hundreds of party supporters. Tinubu’s long convoy proceeded straight to the residence of late Dr. Ahmad Bamba BUK located at Kabuga new extension where he observed his Magrib prayers . Tinubu Pays Condolence Visit To Makinde Over  Olubadan, Soun,… I Endorsed Tinubu For Presidency In 2019, I Have Rejected Him… The National leader of APC while in Kano is expected to visit the residence of late Bashir Othman Tofa, Malam Ado Gwaram, and Dr. Datti Ahmad.